That program refuses to compile not because you can&#x27;t cast to/from arbitrary types in C, but because you don&#x27;t make your intent explicit (assuming I read what you tried to do correctly). Try this:<p><pre><code>    int f(float x) {
        return *(int *)&x;
    }
</code></pre>
On one hand you demonstrate that C cares a tiny little bit about type, but mostly because of implicit numeric conversions rather than any serious attempt at stropping you from bad casting.<p>I do agree with the point that C isn&#x27;t &quot;typeless&quot; in any real sense, though.
